# AI Assistant Context & Rules

## Engineering Principles
- Never assume code works until explicitly validated
- Work as engineering collaborator, challenge assumptions
- Always verify with concrete evidence (builds, tests)

## MCXC143VFM Hardware
- 128KB Flash, 32KB RAM at 0x20000000
- UART2 PTD4/PTD5 @ 115200 (bootloader + app)
- Flash: Production (32KB boot + 92KB app + 4KB config)
- Shell interface CRITICAL - never disable CONFIG_SHELL

## CI/CD Best Practices  
- Use `actions/cache@v4` (auto-save), not `actions/cache/save@v4`
- Docker: `zephyrprojectrtos/zephyr-build:latest` + verify SDK 0.17.4
- Purpose-built images eliminate 5-10min setup time

## Security
- ONE signing key only: `keys/root-ec-p256.pem`
- MCUboot UART programming: copy firmware before reset

## Code Standards
- Relative paths only (workspace portability)
- Files <500-800 lines, split by responsibility  
- Never overwrite source files with redirection (>)
- Zephyr best practices: Device Tree, minimal ISR, work queues

## Development Workflow
1. Test: `target_scripts/test_target_board.py`
2. Build production with commit
3. Update: `target_scripts/firmware_update.py` (~108s)
4. Verify version matches commit hash

